<TITLE> BCB announces preliminary squad for Twenty20 World Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 11 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) Wednesday announced a 30-member preliminary squad for the inaugural Twenty20 World Cup. The Faruque Ahmed-led selection committee has added a few new faces for the meet to be held in South Africa in September. The selected 30 players: Mohammad Ashraful, Aftab Ahmed, Shahriar Nafees, Tamim Iqbal, Tushar Imran, Saqib Al Hasan, Mashrafee Bin Mortaza, Farhad Reza, Abdur Razzak, Mohammad Sharif, Mohammad Rafique, Syed Rasel, Shahadat Hossain, Mahmudullah Riad, Mushfiqur Rahim, Alok Kapali, Tapash Kumar Baishya, Dollar Mahmud, Mohammad Shahazada, Ziaur Rahman, Naeem Islam, Dhiman Ghosh, Junaid Siddique, Jahirul Islam, Nazmus Sadat, Nazimuddin, Nadif Chowdhury, Surawardi Shuvo, Nazmul Hossain Milon and Gazi Salahuddin. 
